# Basic React Program

```jsx
function App() {
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>Welcome to React</h1>
      <p>React makes UI development easy.</p>
    </div>
  );
}

export default App;
```

---

# React Application Structure

A React project commonly contains:

```text
src/
 ├── components/
 ├── App.js
 ├── index.js
 └── styles/
```

---

# Applications of React

React is used to build:

* Social Media Applications
* E-Commerce Websites
* Dashboard Applications
* Real-Time Chat Applications
* Portfolio Websites
* Online Learning Platforms

---

# Conclusion

React is one of the most powerful and widely used frontend libraries for developing modern web applications. Its component-based architecture, Virtual DOM, and fast rendering make development simpler, faster, and more efficient.

React continues to be a top choice for developers and companies building scalable and responsive applications.





